🛠 Installation & Setup
If you'd like to set up the project locally, follow these steps:

Prerequisites:
A text editor (e.g., VS Code, Sublime Text)

Git installed on your computer

Steps:
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/my-portfolio.git
Navigate into the project folder:

bash
Copy
Edit
cd my-portfolio
Open the index.html file in your browser to view the site locally.

Edit the contact form settings by visiting Formspree.io and creating your own form endpoint, replacing the form action URL in the HTML.

🌐 Deployment
The portfolio is deployed on GitHub Pages, but can easily be deployed on platforms like Netlify or Vercel. Here are the steps for GitHub Pages:

Push your project to a GitHub repository.

Go to your repository Settings > GitHub Pages and choose main branch as the source.

Your site will be live at:
https://yourusername.github.io/my-portfolio

